## Version Control

- Follow [conventional commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/): use semantic commit subjects, and include audit-useful rationale/details in the commit body. Also see [Semantic Commit Messages](https://gist.github.com/joshbuchea/6f47e86d2510bce28f8e7f42ae84c7106).

## (Code) Reviews

Reviewer thinking:

1. Prioritize validating the intended goal/outcome -- "Does it build the right thing?"
2. Understand the design and trade-offs; challenge assumptions and rationale -- "Does it build the thing right?"
3. Surface concrete bugs, regressions, risks, and missing tests.
4. Adhere to the conventions and principles -- "Follow the rules until you know when to break them."

Reviewer output:

- List findings first in severity order with file references; keep summary secondary; if there are no findings, say so explicitly and note residual risks or testing gaps.

